  "title": "KYC, SOW, AML Analyst Specialist- 12 Month Contract",
  "description": "<p><em>*1 year contract with a possibility of extension*</em></p><p>Our client is a leading financial services institution supporting ultra-high-net-worth individuals and complex client structures. They are expanding their <strong>AML Risk / Account Management</strong> capability and are looking for experienced professionals in <strong>Source of Wealth (SOW) and AML reviews</strong>.</p><p>This role sits within a specialist AML Risk team responsible for client onboarding reviews, periodic SOW assessments, and complex risk evaluations in line with regulatory expectations.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Review and assess Source of Wealth (SOW) and AML risk profiles for new and existing clients</li><li>Identify gaps, inconsistencies, and corroboration issues in client documentation</li><li>Perform reasonableness and plausibility checks on declared wealth and transaction flows</li><li>Conduct desktop research and benchmarking to support SOW validation</li><li>Engage closely with front office / sales teams to enhance client profiles</li><li>Review adverse findings, sanctions exposure, and high-risk indicators</li><li>Prepare clear AML/SOW risk summaries for escalation to AML Risk Supervisors</li><li>Ensure proper documentation, screening records, and approvals are maintained</li></ul><p><strong>Ideal Profile</strong></p><ul><li><strong>3+ years’ experience</strong> in AML, SOW, or financial crime reviews</li><li>Background from <strong>private banking, wealth management, top-tier banks, or risk advisory firms</strong></li><li>Strong understanding of <strong>AML/CFT frameworks and risk assessment methodologies</strong></li><li>Experience reviewing complex structures (e.g. trusts, SPVs, funds, foundations)</li><li>Strong analytical mindset with high attention to detail</li><li>Confident communicator, able to engage stakeholders and manage sensitive discussions</li><li><strong>Strong written English</strong>; ability to consolidate Chinese and English source information into clear English summaries</li></ul><p><strong>Why This Role</strong></p><ul><li>Exposure to complex, high-value client structures</li><li>Strong learning curve within a specialist AML risk team</li><li>Collaborative, fast-paced environment with high visibility</li></ul>",
